==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portoise
<hw>Por"toise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Perhaps fr. OF.
<ets>porteis</ets> portative, portable.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The gunwale of a ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To lower the yards a-portoise</b></col>, <cd>to lower
them to the gunwale.</cd> -- <col><b>To ride a portoise</b></col>,
<cd>to ride an anchor with the lower yards and topmasts struck or
lowered, as in a gale of wind.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portos</ent>⟦br⟧
